# Coding-agent guidelines for {{ project_slug }}

This project uses **{{ framework_name }}** as the agent framework. When editing this codebase:

## Layout
- `src/{{ project_slug_underscore }}/agents/` — orchestrator and sub-agent factories. Each is a function returning a configured agent.
- `src/{{ project_slug_underscore }}/tools/` — `@tool`-decorated functions; treat as the agent's only side-effect surface.
- `src/{{ project_slug_underscore }}/config/` — Pydantic settings (`settings.py`), model factory (`llm_client.py`), system prompts (`prompts.py`).
- `src/{{ project_slug_underscore }}/ui/` — Streamlit components.

## Conventions
- Tools must be pure functions with type-annotated parameters and a docstring (the LLM reads the docstring as the tool description).
- Never call the LLM client directly inside a tool. Tools return data; the LLM composes the answer.
- Never hardcode credentials. Read all config from `Settings` (loaded from `.env`).
- The `web_search` tool is **mocked** by default — wire to Tavily/Brave/SerpAPI before shipping.

## Testing
- Tools live in `tests/test_example_tools.py` and are unit-tested without invoking the LLM.
- `tests/test_settings.py` verifies env-var loading.
- `make test` runs the suite with coverage.

## Quality gates
- `make lint` — Ruff
- `make typecheck` — ty
- `make test` — pytest
- pre-commit hooks run on every commit (installed by `make install`).
